{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "a8c31b8096d36f4e3eebba51510710c2", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "3. Human Resources Policies", "section": "3.3 Compensation, Payroll & Overtime", "subsection": "3.3.1 Compensation Philosophy", "raw_content": "NexaCorp's compensation philosophy is designed to attract, retain, and motivate high-calibre talent by offering market-competitive total compensation packages. Total compensation comprises base salary, variable pay (short-term and long-term incentives), and benefits. NexaCorp targets the 65th percentile of the relevant talent market for base salary for employees performing at-expectation levels, rising to the 75th percentile for sustained high performers. The relevant talent market is defined annually by the People Analytics team based on industry sector, role type, geographic location, and company size peer group. NexaCorp participates in and purchases data from at least three (3) recognised third-party compensation surveys annually.", "type": "text"}, "page_content": "Part: 3. Human Resources Policies\n            Section: 3.3 Compensation, Payroll & Overtime\n            Subsection: 3.3.1 Compensation Philosophy\n            NexaCorp's compensation philosophy is designed to attract, retain, and motivate high-calibre talent by offering market-competitive total compensation packages. Total compensation comprises base salary, variable pay (short-term and long-term incentives), and benefits. NexaCorp targets the 65th percentile of the relevant talent market for base salary for employees performing at-expectation levels, rising to the 75th percentile for sustained high performers. The relevant talent market is defined annually by the People Analytics team based on industry sector, role type, geographic location, and company size peer group. NexaCorp participates in and purchases data from at least three (3) recognised third-party compensation surveys annually.", "type": "Document"}}